Hawks send 4×100 to State following rainy state-qualifying meet

Rainy weather and a host of problems caused by the rain at the state-qualifying meet on Thursday, May 9, didn’t dampen the spirits of the Lynnville-Sully’s boys track and field team as it put forth incredible effort with hopes of extending its season. PC Track and Field sends athletes to State

Trevor Veenstra will compete at State in two events, the discus and shot put. Weather delays, rain, and cold have been elements area track and field teams have battled all season, and it was no different for the Eagles’ Class 2A State-Qualifying Meet on Thursday, May 9. L-S girls track and field two points short of SICL Conference Championship

The return trip to Iowa Valley on Friday to wrap up the SICL Conference Meet was worth the extra miles as the Hawks' 4x100 team of Tatum Huyser, Morgan Jones, Morgan Hay, and Carsyn McFarland broke its own school record to win gold in 51.59. Hawks claim third in rain-delayed SICL Conference Meet

Hendrick Lowry takes off from the starting line at the SICL Conference Meet. Lowry placed second in the 3200m run and fifth in the 1600m run at conference.
